---
import ToolLayout from '../Layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="About CalCluster — Free Online Calculator Tools"
  description="CalCluster is a free collection of online calculator tools built for students, professionals, and curious minds. No login, no fees, no nonsense."
  canonicalUrl="https://calcluster.com/about/"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">About CalCluster</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-8 text-lg">
      CalCluster is a free, independently built collection of calculator tools for students, professionals, hobbyists, and anyone who needs a fast and reliable answer. No login required. No subscription. No paywalls. Every tool on this site is free to use and always will be.
    </p>

    <hr class="border-slate-200 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Section 1 — Why CalCluster Exists</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Most calculator websites are cluttered, slow, and plastered with aggressive ads that load before the tool does. CalCluster was built as a direct response to that — a clean, fast, minimal site where the calculator loads first and everything else stays out of the way. The goal is simple: give people accurate answers quickly, without friction. We believe you should not have to scroll past auto-playing videos just to do basic math.
    </p>

    <hr class="border-slate-200 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Section 2 — Who It Is For</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      CalCluster is designed for anyone who deals with numbers daily. It is for students working through math, science, and geography problems who need to check their work. It is for architects and engineers verifying drawing dimensions and technical calculations on the fly. Model builders and hobbyists working with scale ratios will find our specialized tools perfectly tailored to their craft. It is for fitness enthusiasts tracking training metrics, and ultimately, anyone who needs a quick reliable calculation without installing an app or signing up for anything.
    </p>

    <hr class="border-slate-200 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Section 3 — How It Works</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      CalCluster is a fully static website — there is no server processing your inputs, no database storing your calculations, and no account required. Every calculator runs entirely in your browser using vanilla JavaScript. Your inputs never leave your device. The site is hosted on Cloudflare Pages, which means it loads fast from anywhere in the world. We ensure there is no tracking, no profiling, and absolutely no data collection from the calculators themselves.
    </p>

    <hr class="border-slate-200 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Section 4 — The Tools</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      We are building a focused library of calculator tools across several categories. Current and planned tools cover areas including scale and proportion, mathematics, fitness and training, sports statistics, astronomy, genetics, and more. Each tool is built to be accurate, clearly explained, and useful for real tasks — not just novelty. Every tool page includes a full explanation of the formula, worked examples, and answers to the most common questions.
    </p>

    <hr class="border-slate-200 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Section 5 — How We Stay Free</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      CalCluster is supported by advertising. Once the tool library reaches a sufficient size, we will apply for Google AdSense to display relevant ads on tool pages. The ads support the ongoing development and hosting costs so the tools remain free for everyone. We have deliberately designed the layout so ads never appear above the fold — the calculator always loads first, ensuring your primary task is never interrupted by intrusive placements.
    </p>

    <hr class="border-slate-200 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Section 6 — Accuracy</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Every formula used on CalCluster is manually verified before any tool is published. Where a calculation has known edge cases — division by zero, invalid inputs, negative figures, or unit mismatches — the tool handles them explicitly with clear error messages rather than producing a silent wrong answer. If you ever find an error in a calculation, please report it via the contact page and we will fix it immediately.
    </p>

    <hr class="border-slate-200 my-10" />

    <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-10 mb-4">Section 7 — Contact and Feedback</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      We genuinely want to hear from users. If a tool is wrong, if a feature is missing, if a new calculator would be useful, or if anything on the site is confusing — tell us. Use the <a href="/contact/" class="text-[#1D9E75] hover:text-[#168561] hover:underline">contact page</a> to send us your thoughts directly. We read every submission and actively prioritize our development based on the community's needs.
    </p>

  </div>
</ToolLayout>